  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Heaven And Earth
---
The Master said The Way - how deep its dwelling, how pure its
clearness! Without it, the bells and chiming stones will not sound. The
bells and stones have voices but, unless they are struck, they will not
sound. The ten thousand things - who can make them be still?
